headline: Ralph Lauren (RL): Evaluating Valuation After a 13% Monthly Surge and 69% One-Year Rally
summary: Ralph Lauren (RL) has quietly turned into one of the market's stronger fashion stories, with the stock up roughly 13% over the past month and nearly 69% over the past year. See our latest analysis for Ralph Lauren. That kind of 12.82 percent 30 day share price return, on top of a 68.75 percent one year total shareholder return, indicates momentum may still be building as investors focus on Ralph Lauren's improving growth story and premium brand positioning.
